abstract = {Cyber-physical system is an exciting digital technology used in agriculture, energy, medicine, transportation, and more. It is gaining interest in academia, government, and business. The cyber-physical power system (CPPS) merges physical equipment with communications and information technologies. The CPPS, a physical system closely linked to cyber systems (control, computation, and communication functions), permits two-way power and information flows for smart grid technologies. Digital technologies monitor and regulate the electrical grid more effectively and reliably, yet the power grid is exposed to risk from cybersecurity and includes complex cyber-physical interdependency. CPPS challenges need modeling and rigorous analysis of a complex cyber-physical interaction. Traditional modeling, training, and analysis separate physical and cyber domains, which is unsuitable for current CPPS. Thus, an integrated framework was required to analyze the real situation of physical-cyber system unification. This study reviews modeling, simulation, analysis, cyberattacks, and cybersecurity measures for current CPPS. This study reviews realistic power system cyberattack detection and mitigation control techniques. Finally, CPPS research worldwide and a new route for suggestions and investigation directions for CPPS researchers are offered.}
